4&amp;filter=0\">web search</a><div><div class=\"hover-container\"><form action=\"http://googlesearch.northwestern.edu/search\" id=\"web-search\" method=\"get\"><input name=\"site\" type=\"hidden\" value=\"mcc\"/><input name=\"client\" type=\"hidden\" value=\"mcc\"/><input name=\"output\" type=\"hidden\" value=\"xml_no_dtd\"/><input name=\"proxystylesheet\" type=\"hidden\" value=\"mcc2014\"/><input name=\"filter\" type=\"hidden\" value=\"0\"/><input autocomplete=\"off\" id=\"q\" name=\"q\" placeholder=\"Search this site\" type=\"search\"/></form></div></div></li><li id=\"top-nav-explore\"><a href=\"../../../explore/index.html\">Explore</a></li></ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<h1 id=\"major-title\"><span class=\"header-container\"><a href=\"../../index.html\">Research and Faculty</a><span class=\"extraneous\">, McCormick School of Engineering, Northwestern University</span></span></h1>\r\n<div id=\"mobile-nav\">\r\n<div id=\"mobile-nav-handle\">\r\n<div id=\"inner\">SECTION MENU</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</header>\r\n<div id=\"container\">\r\n<div id=\"left-col\"><div id=\"section-nav-head\">IN THIS SECTION</div><nav><ul><li><a href=\"../../index.html\">Research and Faculty</a></li><li class=\"active expanded section\"><a href=\"../index.html\">Faculty Directory</a><ul><li class=\"index\"><a href=\"../index.html\">Faculty Directory</a></li><li><a href=\"../faculty-fellows.html\">Faculty Fellows</a></li></ul></li></ul></nav></div>\r\n<div id=\"main-content-wrap\">\r\n<div id=\"main-content\" role=\"main\"><h1 id=\"page-title\"><div>Faculty Directory</div>Koray Aydin</h1><div id=\"faculty-profile-left\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"../../../images/research-and-faculty/directory/aydin-koray.jpg\"/><p class=\"title\">Assistant Professor of Electrical Engineering and Computer Science</p><h2>Contact</h2>2145 Sheridan Road, L359<br/>Tech Room L391<br/>Evanston, IL 60208-3109<br/><br/><a class=\"phone_link\" href=\"tel://847-491-3055\"><span class=\"phone_link_verbose\">847-491-3055</span></a><a class=\"mail_link\" href=\"mailto:aydin@northwestern.edu\">Email <span>Koray&#160;Aydin</span></a><h2 class=\"sites-header\">Website</h2><p><a href=\"http://users.eecs.northwestern.edu/~aydin/MNDL/People.html\" target=\"_blank\">Koray Aydin's Homepage</a></p><p><a href=\"http://users.eecs.northwestern.edu/~aydin/MNDL/Home.html\" target=\"_blank\">Metamaterials and Nanophotonic Devices Lab</a></p><hr/><h2>Departments</h2><p><a href=\"http://eecs.northwestern.edu\" target=\"_blank\">Electrical Engineering and Computer Science</a></p><hr/><p><a href=\"http://mccormick.northwestern.edu/docs/public_cv/Aydin-Koray-CV.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Download CV</a></p></div><div id=\"faculty-profile-right\"><h2>Education</h2><p>Ph.D. in Physics, Bilkent University, Ankara, Turkey</p>\r\n<p>M.S. in Physics, Bilkent University, Ankara, Turkey</p>\r\n<p>B.S. in Physics, Bilkent University, Ankara, Turkey</p><br/><h2>Research Interests</h2><p><div class=\"style_SkipStroke_3 shape-with-text\" id=\"id18\">\r\n<div class=\"text-content graphic_textbox_layout_style_default_External_499_205\">\r\n<div class=\"graphic_textbox_layout_style_default\">\r\n<p class=\"paragraph_style_5\"><span class=\"style_3\">The research program in the </span><span class=\"style_4\">Metamaterials and Nanophotonic Devices Lab </span><span class=\"style_3\">is mainly focused on the broad area of </span><span class=\"style_5\">nanophotonics</span><span class=\"style_3\">, an emerging field strategically positioned at the intersection</span><span class=\"style_4\"> </span><span class=\"style_3\">of </span><span class=\"style_6\">electrical engineering</span><span class=\"style_3\">, </span><span class=\"style_6\">applied physics</span><span class=\"style_3\">, </span><span class=\"style_6\">materials science</span><span class=\"style_3\"> and </span><span class=\"style_6\">nanoscience</span><span class=\"style_3\">. </span><span class=\"style_3\">We are investigating </span><span class=\"style_7\">optical metamaterials</span><span class=\"style_3\">, </span><span class=\"style_7\">plasmonics</span><span class=\"style_3\">, metasurfaces and</span><span class=\"style_7\"> solid-state nanophotonics</span><span class=\"style_3\"> to understand the interaction between light and nanoscale photonic materials and to control and manipulate these interactions at will. Our ultimate aim is to </span><span class=\"style_8\">design</span><span class=\"style_3\">, </span><span class=\"style_8\">fabricate</span><span class=\"style_3\"> and </span><span class=\"style_8\">characterize</span><span class=\"style_3\"> metamaterials and nanophotonic devices with novel optical and photonic functionalities.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"paragraph_style_5\">Current research topics include metamaterials and metasurfaces for ocntrolling light at the subwavelength scale, plasmonic materials and devices for absorption engineering, two-dimensional materials for plasmonic and optoelectronic application, inverse design of compact millimeter wave and optical metadevices, hybrid, active and tunable nanophotonic devices based on phase transition materials. </p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"com-apple-iweb-widget-HTMLRegion\" id=\"widget2\"> </div></p><br/><h2>Selected Publications</h2><ul><p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s2\">Enhanced radiative emission from monolayer MoS2 films using a single plasmonic nanoantenna</span><span class=\"s1\"><br/> E. Palacios, S. Park, S. Butun, L. Lauhon, and K. Aydin</span><span class=\"s3\"><br/> <a href=\"http://aip.scitation.org/doi/abs/10.1063/1.4993427\"><span class=\"s4\"><strong><em>Appl. Phys. Lett.</em></strong> 111, 031101 (2017)</span></a></span><span class=\"s4\">.</span><span class=\"s1\"><br/> </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s3\">I</span><span class=\"s2\">dentifying excitation and emission rate contributions to plasmon-enhanced photoluminescence from monolayer MoS2 using a tapered gold nanoantenna</span><span class=\"s3\"><br/> </span><span class=\"s1\">E. Palacios, S. Park, L. Lauhon, and K. Aydin</span><span class=\"s3\"><br/> <a href=\"http://pubs.acs.org/doi/abs/10.1021/acsphotonics.7b00226\"><span class=\"s4\"><strong><em>ACS Photonics </em></strong>4, 1602 (2017)</span></a></span><span class=\"s4\">.</span> </p>\r\n<p class=\"p3\"><span class=\"s6\">Quantifying plasmon-enhanced light absorption in monolayer WS2 films</span><span class=\"s3\"><br/> </span><span class=\"s2\">S. Butun, E. Palacios, J. Cain, Z. Liu, V. P. Dravid, and K. Aydin<br/> <a href=\"http://pubs.acs.org/doi/full/10.1021/acsami.7b01947\"><span class=\"s1\"><strong><em>ACS Appl. Mat. &amp; Int. </em></strong>9, 15044 (2017)</span></a>.</span> </p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s2\">Wideband, zero-index metacrystal with high transmission at visible frequencies</span><span class=\"s3\"><br/> </span><span class=\"s1\">Z. Li, Z. Liu, and K. Aydin<br/> <a href=\"https://www.osapublishing.org/josab/abstract.cfm?uri=josab-34-7-D13\"><span class=\"s2\"><strong><em>JOSA B</em></strong> 34, D13 (2017)</span></a>.<br/> </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p3\"><span class=\"s6\">Chiral-selective plasmonic metasurface absorbers operating at visible frequencies<br/> </span><span class=\"s2\">B. Tang, Z. Li, E. Palacios, Z. Liu, S. Butun, and K. Aydin<br/> <a href=\"http://ieeexplore.ieee.org/abstract/document/7803536/\"><span class=\"s4\"><strong><em>I</em></strong></span><span class=\"s1\"><strong><em>EEE Phot. Tech. Lett. </em></strong>29, 295 (2017)</span></a>.<br/> </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s2\">Functional metal-insulator top contacts for Si-based color photodetectors<br/> </span><span class=\"s1\">S. Butun, and K. Aydin<br/> <span class=\"s2\"><a href=\"http://aip.scitation.org/doi/full/10.1063/1.4971965\"><strong><em>J. Appl. Phys. </em></strong>120, 223102 (2016).</a></span></span> </p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s2\">Broadband asymmetric light transmission through tapered metallic gratings at visible frequencies<br/> </span><span class=\"s1\">B. Tang, Z. Li, Z, Liu, F. Callewaert, and K. Aydin<br/> <a href=\"http://www.nature.com/articles/srep39166\"><span class=\"s2\"><strong><em>Scientific Reports</em></strong> 6, 39166 (2016)</span></a>.</span> </p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s2\">Enhanced infrared transmission through gold nanoslit arrays via surface plasmons in continuous graphene<br/> </span><span class=\"s1\">Z. Liu, and K. Aydin<br/> <a href=\"https://www.osapublishing.org/oe/abstract.cfm?uri=oe-24-24-27882\"><span class=\"s2\"><strong><em>Optics Express</em></strong> 24, 27882 (2016)</span></a>.</span> </p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s2\">Time-varying metasurfaces based on graphene micro-ribbon arrays<br/> </span><span class=\"s1\">Z. Liu, Z. Li, and K. Aydin<br/> <a href=\"http://pubs.acs.org/doi/abs/10.1021/acsphotonics.6b00653\"><span class=\"s4\"><strong><em>ACS Photonics</em></strong> 3, 2035 (2016)</span></a>.</span> </p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s2\">Inverse design of an ultra-compact broadband optical diode based on asymmetric spatial mode conversion<br/> </span><span class=\"s1\">F. Callewaert, S. Butun, Z. Li, and K. Aydin<br/> <a href=\"http://www.nature.com/articles/srep32577\"><span class=\"s4\"><strong><em>Scientific Reports </em></strong>6, 32577 (2016)</span></a>.<br/> </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p5\"><span class=\"s2\">Omnidirectional and broadband absorption enhancement from trapezoidal Mie resonators in semiconductor metasurfaces<br/> </span><span class=\"s7\">R. Pala, S. Butun, K. Aydin, and H. A. Atwater<br/> <a href=\"http://www.nature.com/articles/srep31451\"><span class=\"s1\"><strong><em>Scientific Reports</em></strong> 6, 31451 (2016).</span></a><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">   </span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p6\"><span class=\"s2\">Localized surface plasmons in nanostructured monolayer black phosphorus<br/> </span><span class=\"s1\">Z. Liu, and K. Aydin<br/> <a href=\"http://pubs.acs.org/doi/abs/10.1021/acs.nanolett.5b05166\"><span class=\"s2\"><strong><em>Nano Letters</em></strong> 16, 3457 (2016)</span></a>.</span>   </p>\r\n<p class=\"p8\"><span class=\"s6\">Ultrawide angle, directional spectrum splitting visible-frequency versatile metasurfaces<br/> </span><span class=\"s2\">Z. Li, E. Palacios, S. Butun, and K. Aydin<br/> <span class=\"s1\"><a href=\"http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1002/adom.201600068/abstract\"><strong><em>Advanced Optical Materials</em></strong> 4, 953 (2016).</a></span></span> </p>\r\n<p class=\"p8\"><span class=\"s6\">Narrow band absorber based on a dielectric nanodisk array on silver film<br/> </span><span class=\"s2\">F. Callewaert, S. Chen, S. Butun, and K. Aydin<br/> <a href=\"http://iopscience.iop.org/article/10.1088/2040-8978/18/7/075006\"><span class=\"s1\"><strong><em>J. of Optics </em></strong>18, 075006 (2016)</span></a>.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p6\"><span class=\"s2\">Lithography-free transmission filters at ultraviolet frequencies using ultra-thin aluminum films<br/> </span><span class=\"s1\">Z. Li, S. Butun, K. Aydin<br/> <a href=\"http://iopscience.iop.org/article/10.1088/2040-8978/18/6/065006\"><span class=\"s2\"><strong><em>J. of Optics </em></strong>18, 065006 (2016)</span></a>.</span>  </p>\r\n<p class=\"p6\"><span class=\"s2\">Asymmetric absorption and reflection in plasmonic nanohole arrays</span><span class=\"s1\"><br/> S. Butun, and K. Aydin<br/> <span class=\"s2\"><a href=\"http://pubs.acs.org/doi/abs/10.1021/acsphotonics.5b00377?journalCode=apchd5\"><strong><em>ACS Photonics </em></strong>2, 1652 (2015).</a></span></span> </p>\r\n<p class=\"p6\"><span class=\"s2\">Broadband metasurfaces for anomalous transmission and spectrum splitting at visible frequencies</span><span class=\"s1\"><br/> Z. Li, and K. Aydin<br/> <a href=\"http://epjam.edp-open.org/articles/epjam/abs/2015/01/epjam150008/epjam150008.html\"><span class=\"s4\"><strong><em>EPJ Appl. Metamat</em></strong>. 2, 2 (2015)</span></a>.</span> </p>\r\n<p class=\"p9\"><span class=\"s2\">Unidirectional lasing from template-stripped two-dimensional plasmonic crystals</span><span class=\"s8\"><br/> A. Yang, Z. Li, M. P. Knudson, A. J. Hryn, W. Wang, K. Aydin, T. W. Odom<br/> <a href=\"http://pubs.acs.org/doi/abs/10.1021/acsnano.5b05419\"><span class=\"s7\"><strong><em>ACS Nano</em></strong>9, 11582 (2015)</span></a></span><span class=\"s7\">.</span> </p>\r\n<p class=\"p6\"><span class=\"s2\">Omnidirectional, broadband light absorption using large-area, ultrathin lossy metallic film coatings<br/> </span><span class=\"s1\">Z. Li, H. Kocer, and K. Aydin<br/> <a href=\"http://www.nature.com/articles/srep15137\"><span class=\"s2\"><strong><em>Scientific Reports</em></strong> 5, 15137 (2015)</span></a>.<br/> </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p6\"><span class=\"s2\">Dynamically controlled plasmonic nano-antenna phased array utilizing vanadium dioxide</span><span class=\"s1\"><br/> G. Kaplan, K. Aydin, and J. Scheuer<br/> <a href=\"https://www.osapublishing.org/ome/abstract.cfm?uri=ome-5-11-2513\"><span class=\"s2\"><strong><em>Optical Materials Express</em></strong> 5, 2513 (2015)</span></a>.</span> </p>\r\n<p class=\"p10\"><span class=\"s9\">Nanostructured Silicon Success </span><span class=\"s10\">(News and Views)</span><span class=\"s2\"><br/> K. Aydin<br/> <span class=\"s1\"><a href=\"http://www.nature.com/nphoton/journal/v9/n6/full/nphoton.2015.89.html\"><strong><em>Nature Photonics</em></strong> 9, 353 (2015)</a>.</span></span> </p>\r\n<p class=\"p5\"><span class=\"s2\">Intensity tunable infrared broadband absorbers based on VO2 phase transition using planar layered thin films<br/> </span><span class=\"s7\">H. Kocer, S. Butun, E. Palacios, Z. Liu, S. Tongay, D. Fu, K. Wang, J. Wu, and K. Aydin<br/></span><a href=\"http://www.nature.com/articles/srep13384\"><span class=\"s1\"><strong><em>Scientific Reports</em></strong> 5, 13384 (2015)</span></a>.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p10\"><span cla