es-header\">Website</h2><p><a href=\"http://users.eecs.northwestern.edu/~anindya/\" target=\"_blank\">Anindya De's Homepage</a></p><hr/><h2>Departments</h2><p><a href=\"http://eecs.northwestern.edu\" target=\"_blank\">Electrical Engineering and Computer Science</a></p><hr/><p><a href=\"http://mccormick.northwestern.edu/docs/public_cv/De-Anindya-CV.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Download CV</a></p></div><div id=\"faculty-profile-right\"><h2>Education</h2><p>Ph.D Computer Science, University of California - Berkeley, Berkeley, CA</p>\r\n<p>B. Tech Computer Science and Engineering, Indian Institute of Technology, Kanpur, India</p><br/><br/><h2>Selected Publications</h2><ul><li>Anindya De, Ryan O'Donnell, Rocco A. Servedio, \"<em>Optimal mean-based algorithms for trace reconstruction</em>\", STOC 2017 - Proceedings of the 49th Annual ACM SIGACT Symposium on Theory of Computing, (2017)</li><li>Anindya De, Michael Saks, Sijian Tang, \"<em>Noisy Population Recovery in Polynomial Time</em>\", Proceedings - 57th Annual IEEE Symposium on Foundations of Computer Science, FOCS 2016, (2016)</li><li>Anindya De, Ilias Diakonikolas, Rocco A. Servedio, \"<em>A Robust khintchine inequality, and algorithms for computing optimal constants in fourier analysis and high-dimensional geometry</em>\", SIAM Journal on Discrete Mathematics, (2016)</li><li>Anindya De, Elchanan Mossel, Joe Neeman, \"<em>Majority is stablest</em>\", Theory of Computing, (2016)</li><li>Constantinos Daskalakis, Anindya De, Christos Tzamos, Gautam Kamath, \"<em>A size-free CLT for Poisson multinomials and its applications</em>\", STOC 2016 - Proceedings of the 48th Annual ACM SIGACT Symposium on Theory of Computing, (2016)</li><li>Anindya De, \"<em>Beyond the Central Limit theorem</em>\", Proceedings - Annual IEEE Symposium on Foundations of Computer Science, FOCS, (2015)</li></ul></div><div style=\"clear: both;\">&#160;</div></div>\r\n  \r\n<div id=\"back-to-top\"><a href=\"#top\">BACK TO TOP</a></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>