r-container\"><form action=\"http://googlesearch.northwestern.edu/search\" id=\"web-search\" method=\"get\"><input name=\"site\" type=\"hidden\" value=\"mcc\"/><input name=\"client\" type=\"hidden\" value=\"mcc\"/><input name=\"output\" type=\"hidden\" value=\"xml_no_dtd\"/><input name=\"proxystylesheet\" type=\"hidden\" value=\"mcc2014\"/><input name=\"filter\" type=\"hidden\" value=\"0\"/><input autocomplete=\"off\" id=\"q\" name=\"q\" placeholder=\"Search this site\" type=\"search\"/></form></div></div></li><li id=\"top-nav-explore\"><a href=\"../../../explore/index.html\">Explore</a></li></ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<h1 id=\"major-title\"><span class=\"header-container\"><a href=\"../../index.html\">Research and Faculty</a><span class=\"extraneous\">, McCormick School of Engineering, Northwestern University</span></span></h1>\r\n<div id=\"mobile-nav\">\r\n<div id=\"mobile-nav-handle\">\r\n<div id=\"inner\">SECTION MENU</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</header>\r\n<div id=\"container\">\r\n<div id=\"left-col\"><div id=\"section-nav-head\">IN THIS SECTION</div><nav><ul><li><a href=\"../../index.html\">Research and Faculty</a></li><li class=\"active expanded section\"><a href=\"../index.html\">Faculty Directory</a><ul><li class=\"index\"><a href=\"../index.html\">Faculty Directory</a></li><li><a href=\"../faculty-fellows.html\">Faculty Fellows</a></li></ul></li></ul></nav></div>\r\n<div id=\"main-content-wrap\">\r\n<div id=\"main-content\" role=\"main\"><h1 id=\"page-title\"><div>Faculty Directory</div>Michael Horn</h1><div id=\"faculty-profile-left\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"../../../images/research-and-faculty/directory/horn-michael.jpg\"/><p class=\"title\">Associate Professor of Electrical Engineering and  Computer Science and Education and Social Policy</p><h2>Contact</h2>2120 Campus Drive<br/>Annenberg Room 336<br/>Evanston, IL 60208-3109<br/><br/><a class=\"phone_link\" href=\"tel://617-803-5501\"><span class=\"phone_link_verbose\">617-803-5501</span></a><a class=\"mail_link\" href=\"mailto:michael-horn@northwestern.edu\">Email <span>Michael&#160;Horn</span></a><h2 class=\"sites-header\">Website</h2><p><a href=\"http://tidal.northwestern.edu/people/mikehorn/\" target=\"_blank\">Michael Horn's Homepage</a></p><p><a href=\"http://eecs.northwestern.edu/~mhorn/\" target=\"_blank\">TIDAL Lab</a></p><hr/><h2>Departments</h2><p><a href=\"http://eecs.northwestern.edu\" target=\"_blank\">Electrical Engineering and Computer Science</a></p><hr/><p><a href=\"http://mccormick.northwestern.edu/docs/public_cv/Horn-Michael-CV.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Download CV</a></p></div><div id=\"faculty-profile-right\"><h2>Education</h2><p>Ph.D. Computer Science, Tufts University, Medford/Somerville, MA</p>\r\n<p>M.S. Computer Science, Tufts University, Medford/Somerville, MA</p>\r\n<p>B.S. Computer Science, Brown University, Providence, Rhode Island</p><br/><h2>Research Interests</h2><p><div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 2\">\r\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\r\n<div class=\"column\">\r\n<p>Michael S. Horn is an assistant professor at Northwestern University with a joint appointment in Computer Science and the Learning Sciences. Michael's research explores the use of emerging interactive technology in the design of novel learning experiences. His projects include the design and evaluation of a tangible computer programming language for use in science museums and early elementary school classrooms; and the design of multi-touch tabletop exhibits for use in natural history museums.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div></p><br/><h2>Selected Publications</h2><ul><li>Michael S. Horn, Brenda C. Phillips, Evelyn Margaret Evans, Florian Block, Judy Diamond, Chia Shen, \"<em>Visualizing biological data in museums</em>\", Journal of Research in Science Teaching, (2016)</li><li>David Weintrop, Elham Beheshti, Michael Horn, Kai Orton, Kemi Jona, Laura Trouille, Uri Wilensky, \"<em>Defining Computational Thinking for Mathematics and Science Classrooms</em>\", Journal of Science Education and Technology, (2016)</li><li>Horn, M. S.; Leong, Z. A.; Block, F.; Diamond, J.; Evans, E. M., \"<em>Of BATs and APEs: An Interactive Tabletop Game for Natural History Museums</em>\", Ann Arbor, (2012)</li></ul></div><div style=\"clear: both;\">&#160;</div></div>\r\n  \r\n<div id=\"back-to-top\"><a href=\"#top\">BACK TO TOP</a></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<footer class=\"cf\" role=\"contentinfo\"><div class=\"header-container cf\"><a href=\"http://www.northwestern.edu\" id=\"footer-logo\" target=\"_blank\">Northwestern Seal</a><div id=\"footer-links\"><p><span class=\"footer-branding-element\">McCormick School of Engineering,</span>&#160;\r\n                        \r\n                        \r\n                        <span class=\"footer-branding-element\">Northwestern University</span></p><address>Technological Institute, 2145 Sheridan Road, Evanston, IL 60208</address><p class=\"contact-info white-single-arrow\"><a href=\"../../../contact/index.html\">view all contact info</a></p><ul><li><a href=\"../../../academics/apply.html\">Admissions</a></li><li><a href=\"../index.html\">Faculty Directory</a></li><li><a href=\"http://giving.northwestern.edu/node/2668\" target=\"_blank\">Give to McCormick</a></li><li><a href=\"../../../contact/maps.html\">Tech Room Finder / Maps</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.mccormick.northwestern.edu/faculty-staff-resources/safety-emergency-information/index.html\">Emergency Information</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.northwestern.edu\" target=\"_blank\">Northwestern Home</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.mccormick.northwestern.edu/offices-services/index.html#lost-and-found\" target=\"_blank\">Tech Lost and Found</a></li></ul></div><div id=\"footer-icons\"><div id=\"footer-icon-set1\"><a class=\"icon-twitter iconset-footer\" href=\"http://twitter.com/NorthwesternEng\" target=\"_blank\">McCormick on twitter</a><a class=\"icon-facebook iconset-footer\" href=\"http://facebook.com/northwesternengineering\" target=\"_blank\">